<h2 id="the-many-costumes-of-asthimo">The Many Costumes of Asthimo</h2>
<p>Since Asthimo is modular, we designed a lot of different components that the child could put together to customize their Asthimo. The two most consistent features between each Asthimo model is Asthimoâ€™s backpack and heart. The inhaler spacer is contained within Asthimoâ€™s backpack. The spacer is detachable and the child could choose to use the inhaler mouthpiece located on Asthimoâ€™s back without the spacer attachment once they are old enough to inhale the medicine properly on their own. The renderings of Asthimo I show off the unfoldable inhaler spacer. The heart on Asthimoâ€™s chest is a dose counter.</p>

<h4 id="asthimo-i">Asthimo I</h4>
<p>Asthimo I is a blocky square robot shape, with a pale blue on white plastic colour scheme. Asthimo I was designed and modeled mainly by my other group members, although as mentioned before, I did help with the original concept sketches.</p>

